<h1>Multimedia Computing</h1>

<h2> Whose should pursue a Multimedia Computing Degree? </h1>
<p> Students who are interested in the types of computing that are used for entertainment, art and aesthetics. The major melds work in the Arts, Mathematics and Computer Science to produce students who are comfortable applying computing to non-traditional applications such as robotics, computer gaming, web production, and arts production. </p>

<h1> Helpful tips </h1>

<ul>
<li>Students must complete Brooklyn College General Pathway Requirements along with the Multimedia Computing major courses to complete their Bachelors of Science Degree in Multimedia Computing. </li>
<li>To enroll in a CIS course, a student must have passed all prerequisite courses in the CIS department with a grade of C or higher. </li>
<li>To enroll in a Math course, a student must have passed all Math prerequisite courses with a D- or better. </li>
</ul>

<h1>List of Multimedia Computing Major Requirements </h1>

